item.title: BIO
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Hello!  My name is Jon Lewis and I am a professional Web Developer, musician, and photographer. I live in Toronto, Ontario, Canada, and graduated out of Fanshawe College in London, Ontario for Multimedia Design & Production. This is my home for all of my online content, pretty much everything I've created and plan to create.  I wanted to create a forum to showcase and discuss my work, so feel free to comment, share and contact me for anything! I am available for new projects and always looking for exciting new opportunities.  Hope you enjoy the experience! -Jon

item.title: WEB
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: I started doing Web Design in High School, and co-op'd at Apogee Recording Studio in Orono, Ontario.  I designed websites for my band at the time, and many other bands in the area.  (My other passion was music ;)) Back in those days, I was confined to Corel Draw and an early version of Adobe Photoshop. I can't even remember what type of text editor I was using! Memories... Anyways, after excelling in Digital Communications in High School, I enrolled in Multimedia Design & Production at Fanshawe College in London, Ontario. This is where I first learned proper HTML, CSS & Javascript among other things, like Graphic Design, Video Production, Flash, 3D & Sound Production.  I decided to focus on Web Production after in graduated in 2005, and found contracts at Ontario Children's Mental Health, and a few other various companies doing short-term contracts. After moving to Toronto, my career has taken me to such agencies as Digital Cement, Thrillworks, Forge Media + Design, and now The Globe and Mail, where I'm currently enjoying working on their Globe Unlimited Subscription Service.

item.title: MUSIC
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: I've loved music ever since I was a little kid growing up in the Northeast of England. Hearing my parents records growing up, and eventually moving to Canada and discovering Rock Music around the age of 9 or 10.  My first real musical crush was Nirvana. They made me want to play guitar and play in a band, and I was lucky enough to get my first guitar for my eleventh birthday.  Ever since then, I've been toiling away in basements and garages all over Southern Ontario, playing dingy little clubs and other not-so dingy clubs! My first real band was called Torsion, which we started in 2001 and went until 2006 when we parted ways. We tried really hard to put out a record, but unfortunately didn't work out the way we planned.  Nonetheless it provided a great basis for learning the art of playing and recording, and we have a number of demos to show for our hard work. Since then, I've played with many different people, but focused mostly on a new project called Synergist with my fellow Torsion-ist drummer Chris Lyttle, and vocalist Craig McCutcheon.  We've been playing around Toronto for a couple of years and recorded a number of songs for a planned full-length album we're going to release independently.  Hopefully this year!   It's been a long road, but I'm sure we'll have plenty of music to show for it. :) Check out the links above!

item.title: Everycup.ca
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: During 2011 & 2012 I got the opportunity to work on a few Tim Hortons campaigns at Thrillworks, we launched Everycup.ca on a new CMS called Filemobile.

item.title: The Globe and Mail
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: In 2013, I started at the Globe and Mail working on the Globe Unlimited Subscription Flow.  It's been a great experience so far! My first exposure to a Java application and a great place to sharpen all of my Front-End Development Skills including Mobile!

item.title: Synergist
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Synergist is the band I currently play in! We're working on our first record as we speak and it's nearing completion, check out samples at Synergistband.com and follow us on Facebook and Twitter!

item.title: Torsion
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: From 2001 to 2006 I played Bass in a band called Torsion.  These were my formative years as a musician and we made some great music together.  I'm in the process of remixing some of our demos as we speak and plan to make as much available online as possible.  Stay tuned for updates!

item.title: Our Friend Mark
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Mark is a good guy. This was our very silly tribute to our good friend back in the day, maybe one day Mark will be resurrected and it will be epic.

item.title: Tim Hortons Coffee Partnership
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: In 2011, we launched a Tim Hortons Coffee Partnership micro-site, highlighting their business partnerships in South American Coffee Production.  This was my first exposure to MooTools.

item.title: Smokers' Helpline
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: In 2011 & 2012 I was a part of a project to launch a micro-site for Smokers' Helpline.  This was built using ASP.Net, HTML, CSS, & jQuery, and using Sitefinity CMS.

item.title: Davies
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: In 2011, my first project at Thrillworks was the re-design of dwpv.com.  We used HTML, CSS, jQuery, Javascript, ASP.Net & Sitecore CMS.

item.title: FCT.ca

item.content:encoded: In 2012, I worked on the re-design for FCT.ca at Forge using HTML, CSS, Javascript & jQuery.

item.title: Apple Canada
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: In 2012, I got the opportunity to work on Apple Canada's website, and participated in the launch of the iPhone 5 and the iPad Mini!

item.title: Welcome to my new site!
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Hi everyone! Welcome to my new online portfolio! It's been long overdue, and delayed partly because of my indecisiveness on the design. I've submitted to my perfectionism and gone with a ThemeForest Template. I thought this one was pretty snazzy ;) In the end, it's most important to get the content up, and I can basically do what I want with this design going forward. Looking forward to keeping you guys updated!
